Febrero

Warning! --> this kata contains Java!
Or I should say my folder for this kata contains Java. I have created a very simple maven 2 project to build the project.
'mvn install' or 'mvn test' should do the trick (if you have maven 2 installed!).

I have decided to give this a go cause I've been trying to work more on katas for a while now but never find the time.
This way I hope to keep at it!
I also intend to push to git 2 versions of the kata (maybe more), my first attempt at it, and another version when I have been
practicing it for a while. I hope to be able to compare and see an evolution from it.

-- Running the specs: //TODO will have to clean this up but only got cuke4duke working now
A full install of JRuby is needed (changing soon to a maven project)
I am using jruby installed through rvm.

Compile all the step definitions with:
javac -cp ~/.rvm/gems/jruby-1.5.6/gems/cuke4duke-0.4.3/lib/cuke4duke-0.4.3.jar features/step_definitons/cukes/*.java

To execute the specs use somehting like (modify paths accordingly):
cuke4duke --jars lib/ --require features/step_definitons/ --require ~/.rvm/gems/jruby-1.5.6/gems/cuke4duke-0.4.3/lib/cuke4duke-0.4.3.jar features
To run from command line, Pico container is needed in lib, and a full JRuby installation is needed too. 
Can install everything through maven and run specs as part of a target, but for now, this is good enough!

Peligro! --> esta kata contiene Java!
La kata ha sido desarrollada con Java y maven. Para construir el proyecto, usando 'mvn install' o 'mvn test' debería ser suficiente.

He decidido seguir este proyecto porque llevo un tiempo queriendo hace más katas pero nunca tengo tiempo. A ver si de esta
forma soy un poco mas consistente!
Voy a subir dos versiones de la kata, la primera vez que la complete, y otra versión despues de haberla hecho unas cuantas veces. 
La intención es poder comparar las dos soluciones y ver si he evolucionado algo durante ese periodo.

Jos - February 2o11
